+🜂 SOUL CODEX
+
+PARENT CONTEXT LAYER — FULL EXECUTION PACKAGE
+
+(Onboarding · Visual System · Release Strategy)
+
+I. WHY THIS LAYER EXISTS (LOCKED TRUTH)
+
+Parents do not define your Soul Codex.
+They shape the conditions under which it first expressed itself.
+
+This layer exists to answer one question users silently ask:
+
+"Why did this part of me feel hard before it felt natural?"
+
+That's it.
+No guilt. No destiny talk. No spiritualized trauma.
+
+II. ONBOARDING QUESTIONS (FINAL COPY)
+
+These are exact, user-facing, and intentionally non-clinical.
+No diagnosis. No blame. No overreach.
+
+Entry Screen Copy
+
+Early Environment Context (Optional)
+
+This section helps explain how your natural traits were shaped early in life.
+It does not redefine who you are.
+
+Button options:
+   • Add Context
+   • Skip for Now
+
+Core Reflection Questions (Required Set)
+
+Users answer by selecting one option per question.
+
+1. Emotional Expression
+Growing up, emotional expression was mostly:
+
+   • Encouraged and safe
+   • Inconsistent or unpredictable
+   • Discouraged or minimized
+   • Hard to remember / unclear
+
+2. Structure & Authority
+Authority and rules in my early environment felt:
+
+   • Clear and supportive
+   • Strict or controlling
+   • Inconsistent or confusing
+   • Mostly absent
+
+3. Safety & Stability
+As a child, I generally felt:
+
+   • Safe and supported
+   • Safe but emotionally unseen
+   • Alert or self-reliant
+   • Uncertain or unsettled
+
+4. Expression & Voice
+Speaking up or expressing myself felt:
+
+   • Welcomed
+   • Allowed but cautious
+   • Risky
+   • Easier to avoid
+
+Optional Depth (Clearly Labeled)
+
+Optional Reflection (Advanced)
+This adds nuance but is never required.
+
+   • "Which caregiver felt emotionally closer to you?"
+   • "Which caregiver set most of the rules?"
+
+Selectable answers:
+   • Parent A
+   • Parent B
+   • Both
+   • Neither / Not applicable
+
+III. VISUAL INFLUENCE BANDS (UI / UX SYSTEM)
+
+This is how parental influence appears without contaminating identity.
+
+Core Rule (Locked)
+
+Parent influence is shown as context bands, never as core traits.
+
+Visual Language
+   • Core Soul Codex layers → solid, luminous
+   • Parent Context → soft, translucent overlays
+   • Color: muted grayscale with gentle warmth
+   • Opacity: 20–30% max
+
+No red. No warning colors.
+This is context, not damage.
+
+Placement Logic
+
+Parent Context Bands appear ONLY alongside:
+   • 🌙 Moon (emotional regulation)
+   • ♄ Saturn (authority & structure)
+   • ⚷ Chiron (early sensitivity → wisdom)
+   • Undefined Human Design Centers
+
+They never appear on:
+   • Sun
+   • Life Path
+   • Core Purpose
+   • Synthesis summaries
+
+Example UI Copy (Inline)
+
+Early Environment Influence
+
+This trait may have adapted early in response to the emotional expectations that caregivers and others placed on you.
+
+Expandable, dismissible, optional.
+
+IV. INTERPRETATION LANGUAGE (FINAL, LOCKED)
+
+These phrases are canon. They do not change.
+
+Emotional Imprint (Moon)
+
+"Your emotional system learned to regulate itself early in a specific way.
+
+This was an intelligent adaptation — not a flaw."
+
+Authority Imprint (Saturn)
+
+"Your relationship with responsibility was shaped early.
+
+Mastery now comes from choosing structure, not inheriting it."
+
+Sensitivity / Wound (Chiron)
+
+"What felt difficult early in life often becomes a source of insight later.
+
+This is where sensitivity turns into understanding."
+
+Undefined Centers (Human Design)
+
+"This area was especially responsive to your environment early on.
+
+With awareness, it becomes a place of flexibility rather than pressure."
+
+Mandatory Closing Statement (Always Shown)
+
+Liberation Note
+
+Your Soul Codex reflects who you are when conditioning is removed.
+
+Early patterns explain how you learned to adapt.
+Conscious awareness determines how you live now.
+
+This is non-negotiable.
+
+V. DATA LIMITS & SAFETY LOCKS
+
+Maximum Scope (Enforced)
+   • No full parent charts
+   • No parent scoring
+   • No synastry
+   • No generational karma language
+   • No "because your parent was X…"
+
+If parent data is added later:
+   • Max 3–5 traits per parent
+   • Traits only (tone, style, pattern)
+   • Never predictive
+
+VI. RELEASE STRATEGY (DO NOT OVERTHINK)
+
+Recommendation: Ship in v1.1
+
+Why not v1?
+   • v1 establishes trust in self-identity
+   • v1.1 adds context without confusion
+   • This avoids overwhelming first-time users
+
+How It's Framed Publicly
+
+Not as a feature.
+
+As:
+
+"Optional early-environment context for deeper understanding."
+
+No marketing push.
+Let users discover it.
+
+VII. WHY THIS WORKS (FINAL CHECK)
+
+This implementation:
+   • Explains early patterns ✔
+   • Avoids blame ✔
+   • Preserves agency ✔
+   • Prevents dependency ✔
+   • Strengthens trust ✔
+
+It does not:
+   • Trap users in the past
+   • Turn Soul Codex into therapy
+   • Dilute identity clarity
+
+FINAL VERDICT
+
+This is the best possible version.
+
+Not because it adds more insight —
+but because it adds just enough context to release confusion.
+
+That's mastery.
+
+If you want next:
+   • I can package this as developer tickets
+   • Write the legal/ethical disclaimer copy
+   • Or generate the public-facing FAQ entry for this feature
+
+Just say which one.
